Entrypoint directory:
    All scripts under this directory and sub-directories should be run from this directory. All the script-paths are relative to this directory.
    To use these scripts in any other bash script do a 'cd' to this directory first in a sub-shell, e.g., (cd root_dir && ./xyz.sh)

Entry script:
    ./.setup: call this for installation

Installers:
    ./androidstudio_installer.sh: this is the main installer
    ./installers/androidstudio_installer_from_binary.sh: installs from downloaded binary. This is the default installation. But, you need to update the download link periodically in the script.
    ./installers/androidstudio_installer_from_official_repo.sh: installs using official repository
    ./installers/androidstudio_installer_with_snap.sh: installs using snap
    ./installers/androidstudio_configurer.sh: mainly enable hardware acceleration


Uninstallers:
    ./androidstudio_uninstaller.sh: this is the main uninstaller
    ./uninstallers/androidstudio_uninstaller_from_binary.sh: removed the binary directly from /opt/android-studio
    ./uninstallers/androidstudio_uninstaller_from_official_repo.sh: uninstalls using apt
    ./uninstallers/androidstudio_uninstaller_with_snap.sh: uninstalls using snap

Note:
    Use 'sdkmanager' command to list, install, update, uninstall packages. See 'sdkmanager --help'
